{
  "message": "fuzz(block-aligned-vec): 25 structured opcode-stream seeds\n\nExisting 10 seeds left the AlignedVec opcode stream sparsely\ncovered. Add 25 seeds that exercise each opcode combination across\nthe relevant alignment / length boundaries:\n\n  opcodes (b%6):\n    0 = AlignedVec::new(len, requested_alignment)\n    1 = AlignedVec::from_vec(payload, requested_alignment)\n    2 = mutate_slice(start, len, fill)\n    3 = clone roundtrip\n    4 = into_vec \u2192 from_vec roundtrip\n    5 = noop\n\n  alignment requests:\n    * 0 / 1 (normalized to 1)\n    * power-of-two (2, 4, 8, 16, 64, 4096, 8192)\n    * non-power-of-two (12, 100, 4097)\n    * over MAX_ALIGNMENT_POWER (8193 \u2192 saturates to 8192)\n\n  length boundaries:\n    * 0 / 1 / 8 / 16 / 32 / 64 / 128 / 512 (max)\n\n  scenarios:\n    * chained replace_with_new at varying alignments (downgrade then upgrade)\n    * full cycle: new \u2192 from_vec \u2192 mutate \u2192 clone \u2192 into_vec \u2192 clone\n    * mutate at start / middle / end / full-slice\n    * empty-vec mutate (no-op guard)\n    * triple-clone idempotency, triple-into_vec rebuild\n    * scattered noops between meaningful ops\n\n188K runs / 11s post-seed surface no crashes.",
